- cs.GT (Game Theory): The paper is primarily concerned with multi-player graph games with partial-observation and parity objective, which falls under the domain of game theory. 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science): The paper discusses the decidability and complexity of various game scenarios, which involves logical reasoning and formal methods. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper deals with games with partial-observation, which is a common problem in AI research. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper establishes tight complexity bounds for various game scenarios, which involves algorithmic analysis and data structures. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper also discusses the connections between multi-player graph games and partial-observation stochastic games, which falls under the domain of systems and control.
